VIEWERS of ‘Aridhio’ programme aired by Tanzania Broadcasting Corporation (TBC) will be treated to a style as Minister of Information, Communication and Communication Technology, Mr Nape Nnauye, is today expected to be the presenter. In a brief video clip circulated by TBC on Sunday, Mr Nape said he will host the programme to highlight progress achieved in his docket during President Samia Suluhu Hassan’s one year in office. By hosting the 120 minutes’ TV programme which starts at 7:00 today, Mr Nape will be taking a different and unique approach in highlighting the achievements of President Samia, which other cabinet ministers have also used. “Welcome to 120 minutes of TBC Aridhio, my name is Nape Nnauye; I am the Minister for Information, Communication and Information Technology. I will take you through 120 minutes of TBC Aridhio that is specifically focusing on one year of President Samia in office. “We know she has done a lot and I will take the 120 minutes to highlight on a lot of things, which have been done during the past one year. I will be your presenter and don’t miss on March 14 (today),” the minister said in the video clip. A number of other government ministers have recently held similar press conferences in which they dwelt on progress made by President Samia one-year reign in office.